   BOLI rules are contained in Oregon Administrative Rules Chapter 839 and are posted to the <a href="https&#58;//secure.sos.state.or.us/oard/processLogin.action">Secretary of State’s Administrative Rules Database</a> within 30 days after adoption. For additional access to statewide administrative rule information, visit the <a href="/transparency/Pages/administrative-rules.aspx">Oregon Transparency Administrative Rules webpage</a>.&#160;</div><div><br></div><div>If you would like to comment on BOLI proposed rules, <a href="/boli/about/Pages/Rulemaking-Public-Comment-Form.aspx" target="_blank">please use this form</a>.<br>
&#160;</div><div>If you would like to be put on our Rules Notice list, please enter your name, email address and a password of your choice at&#58;&#160;<a href="http&#58;//listsmart.osl.state.or.us/mailman/listinfo/boli_rules" style="background-color&#58;#ffffff;">http&#58;//listsmart.osl.state.or.us/mailman/listinfo/boli_rules</a><br><br></div><div><p><strong>2025 Rulemaking Planning Calendar (subject to change)&#58;</strong><br></p><ul><li><strong>June 2025&#58;</strong> Notice of Proposed Rulemaking – Division 25 – Delivery Drivers on Public Works Projects</li><li><strong>July 2025&#58;</strong> Notice of Proposed Rulemaking – Various (if necessary) – Implement legislation adopted by 2025 Legislative Assembly&#160;<br></li><ul><li>Rule Adoption – Division 25 – Quarterly Prevailing Wage Rate Determination<br></li></ul><li><strong>October 2025&#58;</strong>&#160;Rule Adoption – Division 25 – Quarterly Prevailing Wage Rate Determination&#160;<br></li></ul><br></div><div>
